Here is a polished version of your rule set that is short, clear, and production-ready. No comments, no arrows, no fluff, and aligned with modern frontend best practices.

⸻

Engineering Rules

Code Style
• Never use if conftion without braces, use braces in fucntions, condtions, clarity over small code tricks.
• Use function names that clearly describe behavior.

Architecture
• Prefer proven production libraries over building custom solutions:
• Data: TanStack Query, TanStack Table
• UI: Shadcn UI
• State: Zustand
• Forms: React Hook Form
• Animations: Framer Motion

Performance
• Avoid unnecessary re-renders by extracting handlers into named functions.
• Use stable references for callbacks, queries, and memoized values.
• Use virtualization, infinite queries, and batching for large lists.

API and Data
• Use cursor-based pagination with deterministic sort order.
• Always return nextCursor and hasMore.
• Invalidate cursor when filters or sort change.

UI Behavior
• Use skeletons, placeholders, and progressive rendering from Shadcn components.
• Prefer infinite scrolling with TanStack Query for large datasets.
• Keep UI predictable by using named event handlers.
